This paper deals with the vulnerability of neural network image classifiers to adversarial images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The study also involves evaluating the effect of JPG compression on the classification of adversarial images, which falls under the category of image compression (cs.MM) and potentially computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the use of adversarial images and their impact on neural networks is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
